The paper discusses a new training paradigm for deep neural networks that improves model performance by leveraging information from the complement classes. This is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given that the paper covers multiple tasks ranging from computer vision to natural language understanding, it is likely to be relevant to these sub-categories.
